<HL>
   International Brief -- Hambros PLC:
   Pretax Profit Increased 10%,
   Boosted by Banking Unit
</HL>
<DATE>
06/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10
</SO>
<CO>
   U.HBR
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Hambros PLC, a British merchant bank and financial
services concern, said pretax profit rose 10% in the year
ended March 31.
   Pretax profit was #75.3 million ($129.8 million), up from
a restated #68.7 million a year earlier. Hambros had reported
its pretax profit as #70.2 million the year earlier. Hambros
said it restated its 1989 accounts to reflect changes in
accounting methods applied to deferred costs.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Net profit attributable to shareholders rose 42% to #59.2
million from a restated #41.6 million a year earlier. Net
profit for the year-earlier period was initially reported as
#41.9 million.
   Per-share earnings rose 15% to 28.9 pence from a restated
25.1 pence. Per-share earnings were first reported at 25.3
pence.
   The dividend for the year is 11.5 pence a share, up 15%
from 10 pence.
   Hambros linked its profit growth to a 74% jump in profit
from its Hambros Bank PLC operation. Hambros Bank's pretax
profit rose to #64.1 million from #36.8 million a year
earlier.
</TEXT>
